function min_race_time(tires, changeTime, numLaps) {
    const n = tires.length;
    const times = tires.map(([fi, ri]) => fi + (numLaps - 1) * ri);
    let min_time = Math.min(...times) + (numLaps - 1) * changeTime;

    for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        for (let j = 0; j < n; j++) {
            if (i != j) {
                min_time = Math.min(min_time, times[i] + times[j] - tires[i][0] + (numLaps - 2) * changeTime);
            }
        }
    }
    return min_time;
}
```

    1. Find the time it takes each tire to finish the race (`numLaps` laps).
2. Calculate the minimum time to finish the race using only one tire type (minimum time among all tire types) with the time penalty for every lap except the first one.
3. Calculate the minimum time to finish the race using two different tire types. For that, iterate through every pair of distinct tires (i, j) and calculate the total time spent using i tire for the first lap and j for the rest (numLaps - 1) laps with the time penalty for every lap except the first two (same tire can be used in the second lap without waiting).
4. Return the minimum time obtained in steps 2 and 3.

